      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement is a phenomenon where two or more particles become linked so that the state of one instantly influences the state of the other, regardless of the distance between them. Unlike regular correlation, which implies a causal relationship or a shared cause based on prior events, entanglement connects particles in a way that only quantum mechanics describes, meaning their properties are undefined until measured. This \"spooky action at a distance\" allows for instantaneous connections that no classical physical theory can explain, making it a unique feature of the quantum world.",
